The alternative release scenario considered for the refrigeration system involves the release of 19,168 pounds of ammonia over a 10.2 minute period due the development of a break in the sight glass drain of the high pressure receiving vessel .  Under alternative release weather conditions, ammonia could travel 1 mile before dispersing enough to no longer pose a hazard to the public.  This distance is calculated using RMP Comp, a air modeling method allowable under the Risk Management Program.

The alternative release scenario for the refrigeration system is unlikely for the following reasons'

7 Industry standards have been followed for the manufacture and quality control of these units;
7 Ammonia is not corrosive to the equipment in this service;
7 Most of the lines are elevated to minimize potential damage from fork lifts;
7 The facility has preventive maintenance program in place to maintain the on-going integrity of the system;
7 The facility has a training program designed to ensure that the system is operated by qualified personnel; and,
7 The facility emergency response procedures enable trained personnel to respond quickly to isolate any potential releases by closing isolation valves and liquid lines.

